    <abstract id="aspace_eb4a5a6ffaec67def33e7f89384eb064">Peter Drucker is an activist, historian, and writer specializing in U.S. and international politics for over twenty years. The Peter Drucker Oral History Collection (dated 1986-1989) consists of eight interviews conducted by Drucker between 1986-1989. The interviews were used in Drucker's 1994 book, <emph render="italic">Max Shachtman and His Left: A Socialist's Odyssey through the American Century</emph>.</abstract>
